          "text": "For llame, compaction is a separate model call followed by history replacement. The summary is neither merged into the system prompt nor wrapped in `<system-reminder>`.\n\n### llame today\n\nCompaction request:\n\n```text\nSYSTEM:\n  Exact system prompt used by the just-finished turn\n\nMESSAGES:\n  Previous compaction summary, if any, as historical user content\n  Older user/assistant turns being absorbed\n  USER: “Summarize the conversation above...”\n```\n\nThat final summarization instruction is explicit in [compaction.ts](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/apps/api/src/compaction/compaction.ts:33). Reusing the same system prompt and history prefix is intentional for prompt-cache reuse.\n\nThe result is stored separately in the `compactions` lineage with `uptoSeq`; original messages are not deleted.\n\nThe next normal request becomes:\n\n```text\nSYSTEM:\n  Current model’s effective system prompt\n\nMESSAGES:\n  USER:\n    Summary of the earlier conversation...\n    {stored summary}\n\n  Recent uncompacted user/assistant turns\n\n  USER:\n    {current message}\n```\n\nThat leading user-role insertion is implemented in [context-builder.ts](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/apps/api/src/chats/context-builder.ts:198).\n\nIf the current message also switches models:\n\n```text\nSYSTEM:\n  New model’s effective prompt\n\nMESSAGES:\n  USER: {compaction summary}\n  ...\n  USER:\n    <system-reminder>\n    You are now running as model \"new-model-id\".\n    ...\n    </system-reminder>\n\n    {current message}\n```\n\nSo:\n\n- Compaction summary = historical data, leading user-role checkpoint.\n- Model-switch reminder = server-authored control metadata near the triggering user message.\n- System prompt = current authoritative behavioral contract.\n\nMixing the summary into the system prompt would incorrectly elevate fallible summarized conversation content to system authority.\n\n### Reference implementations\n\n| System | Summary generation | Post-compaction representation |\n|---|---|---|\n| llame | Same system/history, final synthetic user summarization instruction | Leading user-role historical summary |\n| Claude Code | Same system prompt, tools, history, plus final user summarization instruction | Replaces conversation layer; system remains unchanged |\n| Codex | Local path appends a synthetic user checkpoint request; OpenAI providers can use server-side `/compact` | Local path installs prefixed summary as user-role history; remote path installs returned compaction items |\n| OpenCode | Separate tool-free request containing serialized history and structured summary template | User-role `<conversation-checkpoint>` containing summary plus retained recent context |\n\nClaude Code’s official documentation confirms that compaction preserves the system layer, sends a one-off summarization request using the existing prefix, and replaces only conversation history. It also reloads project context such as root `CLAUDE.md` after compaction. The exact wire role of Claude Code’s resulting summary is not publicly specified. [Claude Code prompt-caching documentation](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/prompt-caching), [context-window documentation](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/context-window).\n\nCodex’s open-source local path generates a checkpoint summary and installs it as a user-role message, not system instructions. It also has a remote compaction path for supported OpenAI providers. [Codex local compaction](https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/56395bddaf26eb2829387ca6a417bf9128e5b239/codex-rs/core/src/compact.rs#L323-L370), [user-role replacement](https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/56395bddaf26eb2829387ca6a417bf9128e5b239/codex-rs/core/src/compact.rs#L648-L660).\n\nOpenCode is the most explicit: it renders the stored result as `<conversation-checkpoint>` and states that it is historical context, not new instructions. [OpenCode compaction](https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode/blob/fab213312927ea64cf968832c527206e8c944f9e/packages/core/src/session/compaction.ts#L161-L223), [checkpoint serialization](https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode/blob/fab213312927ea64cf968832c527206e8c944f9e/packages/core/src/session/runner/to-llm-message.ts#L147-L165).\n\nRecommendation: keep llame’s three layers separate, but replace the current plain-prose summary format with a structured checkpoint similar to OpenCode/Codex. Plain prose is easier to generate but worse at preserving constraints, exact identifiers, failed approaches, and remaining work.\n\nDecision 1 remains: should per-model chat prompts govern normal chat execution and its compaction call, while title generation keeps its dedicated task prompt? Recommended: yes.",
