          "input": "const patch = \"*** Begin Patch\\n*** Add File: /tmp/llame-issue-153.md\\n+## Problem\\n+\\n+This is the deferred recovery path for a conversation whose historical prefix cannot fit any single available model request.\\n+\\n+The `model-specific-system-prompts` design now handles the ordinary model-downgrade case narrowly: when chat history fits the previous model `A` but not the selected model `B`, the worker uses `A` and `A`'s last immutable context snapshot to produce a transition checkpoint before invoking `B`.\\n+\\n+That still leaves real entry states where no capable source execution context exists:\\n+\\n+1. Model `A` is no longer configured, credentialed, reachable, or otherwise executable.\\n+2. A public-chat fork owns only the portable content exposed by the share—messages and any summaries the fork contract exposes—not the source owner's model snapshots, prompt receipts, credentials, or private metadata.\\n+3. Imported or cloned portable history is already larger than the selected model's context window.\\n+\\n+A single summarizer request over the full prefix fails for the same reason as the target request: the input is already over-window. The current change deliberately fails these cases with `context_incompatible`; it does not silently truncate, cross an ownership boundary, or select a fallback model.\\n+\\n+## Proposed direction: progressive bounded folding\\n+\\n+Fold message-boundary-respecting segments through the selected available model, keeping every inference within that model's real input and reserved-output budget:\\n+\\n+```text\\n+messages 1..N, current user U\\n+\\n+segment 1..K\\n+  -> summarize\\n+  -> S1\\n+\\n+S1 + segment K+1..M\\n+  -> summarize\\n+  -> S2\\n+\\n+S2 + segment M+1..P\\n+  -> summarize\\n+  -> S3\\n+\\n+...\\n+\\n+final checkpoint + retained recent tail + U\\n+  -> ordinary target-model inference\\n+```\\n+\\n+The triggering user message `U` stays outside every summarization step. Segment sizes are computed from tokens, the selected model's configured window, its exact current prompt/tool prefix, the compaction instruction, and reserved summary output—not a fixed message count. Tool schemas may remain byte-equivalent for cache alignment, but every summarization call uses schema-only tools plus `toolChoice: \\\"none\\\"` and has no executors.\\n+\\n+Intermediate and final summaries are generated orientation data, not canonical evidence. Original user/assistant messages remain the searchable/auditable source; summaries and checkpoint envelopes remain outside chat search.\\n+\\n+## Security and provenance invariants\\n+\\n+- Never read another owner's run snapshot, prompt receipt, credentials, reasoning, tool payloads, or non-public metadata to rescue a public fork.\\n+- Use only the portable content the new chat actually owns.\\n+- Never silently drop a segment or substitute another model.\\n+- Record the exact source message range covered by every fold and preserve lineage to the preceding fold.\\n+- A retry must be idempotent; a crash must not leave a checkpoint claiming to cover messages it did not summarize.\\n+- If even one atomic portable message cannot fit the selected model after accounting for prompt and output reserve, fail explicitly rather than truncate it invisibly.\\n+\\n+## Open design work\\n+\\n+- Decide whether intermediate folds are persisted as compaction-lineage rows or remain resumable job state until one final checkpoint commits.\\n+- Define token-budget accounting across providers and how conservative estimation is calibrated against reported usage.\\n+- Bound recursive-summary drift and add evals for lost constraints, reversed decisions, stale state, and fabricated facts.\\n+- Define cancellation, retry, concurrent-run, and compaction-staleness behavior.\\n+- Decide how large individual messages or portable attachments are externalized or rejected.\\n+- Surface progressive compaction in the existing collapsed compaction UI without exposing generated summaries through search.\\n+\\n+## Acceptance\\n+\\n+- A model switch whose prior model is unavailable can continue using only bounded calls to the selected model when every atomic item is individually representable.\\n+- A large public-chat fork can complete its first turn without reading any source-owner private state.\\n+- Every summarization request and the final target request stay below the selected model's input plus reserved-output budget.\\n+- The current user message is never summarized before its own inference.\\n+- No original message is silently omitted, and each fold has auditable source-range lineage.\\n+- Generated summaries do not enter web chat search or `search_conversations`; original messages remain canonical and searchable.\\n+- Failure, cancellation, and retry tests prove no partial checkpoint is presented as complete.\\n+- Quality evals cover multi-stage accumulation, including at least one history requiring three or more folds.\\n+\\n+## Scope relationship\\n+\\n+This issue is intentionally **not** part of `model-specific-system-prompts`. That change owns source-model transition compaction and the explicit `context_incompatible` failure when no capable source context exists. This issue replaces that accepted broken state with progressive bounded folding.\\n+\\n+Refs: #57 (compaction), #130 (public-chat forks), #141 (owner forks), #154 (owner-fork compaction cloning).\\n*** End Patch\";\ntext(await tools.apply_patch(patch));\n",
